check current ubuntu version: $ lsb_release -a
check current kernel version: $ uname -r
check installed linux image: $ dpkg --get-selections |grep linux-image
check installed linux packages: $ dpkg --get-selections |grep linux
install specific package: $ apt-get install linux-headers-4.15.0-213-generic linux-image-4.15.0-213-generic 
choose the specific kernel version: during start process, enter button 'shift' to enter the grub mode and then choose the specific kernel
delete other kernels: apt --purge xxx
